# Anamorphic Test 50mm 2x — synthetic test prescription for FlareSim
#
# DESIGNED FROM SCRATCH for FlareSim Level-3 cylindrical-trace validation.
# This is not a real product.  Optical image quality is mediocre — the
# point is to produce ghosts whose geometry demonstrably goes through
# real cylindrical surfaces, not to match any specific commercial lens.
#
# Layout (11 surfaces):
#   0..3 : Front afocal cylindrical attachment, 2x squeeze.
#          Axes vertical (cyl_y) → curve in XZ → horizontal compression.
#          Plano-concave  (F ≈ -97 mm)
#          + 92 mm air gap
#          + Plano-convex (F ≈ +194 mm).
#          Angular magnification = -F1/F2 ≈ 0.5  →  2x squeeze.
#   4..10: Spherical Petzval-style taking lens, ~50 mm equivalent FL.
#
# Effective focal lengths after the afocal block:
#   horizontal (squeezed): ~25 mm
#   vertical   (unchanged): ~50 mm
#   ratio = 0.5  →  classic 2x anamorphic.
#
# Validation hints (M6 of ANAMORPHIC_LEVEL3_PLAN.md):
#   1. Ghosts of a horizontal point source should elongate vertically;
#      ghosts of a vertical point source should elongate horizontally.
#   2. Sweeping a bright source horizontally across the optical axis
#      should produce a strong horizontal Fresnel streak from the cyl_y
#      bounce pair (surfaces 0 ↔ 3) — the "anamorphic signature".
#   3. The pair filter should keep noticeably MORE pairs than a comparable
#      all-spherical lens because the cylindrical reflections create new
#      ghost families that didn't exist before.
#
# Caveat: only cyl_y surfaces are used (no toric).  That's intentional —
# this file is meant to exercise M1..M3, not M4/M5.

name: Anamorphic Test 50mm 2x
focal_length: 50.0

surfaces:
# radius     thickness   ior      abbe   semi_ap   coating  type
# --- Front afocal cylindrical attachment (2x squeeze, axes vertical) ---
  -50.0      8.00        1.51680  64.2   45.0      1        cyl_y     # plano-concave neg, F ≈ -97
  0          92.00       1.00000  0.0    45.0      0                  # flat back; 92 mm air gap
  0          10.00       1.51680  64.2   40.0      1                  # flat front of pos cyl
  -100.0     15.00       1.00000  0.0    40.0      0        cyl_y     # plano-convex pos, F ≈ +194

# --- Spherical Petzval-style taking lens, ~50 mm ----------------------
# Semi-apertures are kept just under each surface's radius (semi_ap < |R|)
# so every spherical surface is geometrically valid.  Off-axis ghost
# rays through the cylindrical bounce-pair (0,3) will mostly vignette
# at this taking lens — that's actual anamorphic-lens physics, not a
# bug.  The cylindrical signature is still clearly visible in the
# small pupil region that does get through.
  45.0       6.00        1.51680  64.2   22.0      1                  # crown front (doublet 1)
  -30.0      2.00        1.62000  36.0   22.0      1                  # cemented junction
  -90.0      8.00        1.00000  0.0    20.0      0                  # back of D1, air gap
  stop       8.00        1.00000  0.0    14.0      0                  # aperture stop
  90.0       2.00        1.62000  36.0   20.0      1                  # flint front (doublet 2)
  30.0       6.00        1.51680  64.2   22.0      1                  # cemented junction
  -45.0      35.00       1.00000  0.0    22.0      0                  # back of D2 -> sensor
